mslRemarks: The amount of sewage sludge which is mentionend under 'mslReuseOhters' is composted in Luxembourg. The amount of sewage sludge which is written under 'mslDisposalOthers' is the amount of sludge who is incinerated in Germany (775 t DS/y) and in Belgium  (462 t DS/y), composted (1558 t DS/y) in France and used in agriculture (82 t DS/y) in Germany.
There is no waste water re-use in Estonia. mslDisposalOthers represents sludge that stays in the storage (i.e disposed in special depot sites).

mslWWReusePerc: 88% used in TP for irrigation/washing. 12% used by external entities (ERSAR-RASARP 2021).
mslReuseOthers: Waste recovery operation R3-Recycling/recovery of organic substances not used as solvents (anaerobic digestion, composting, other).

The 6918 t DS/y mentioned in others refers to 508 t DS/y of sludge tranported for anaerobic treatment for biogas production, 4682 t DS/y of sludge tranported for compost production and to 1728 t DS/y of sludge storaged at the plants to be  reused.
